Automate PLC variable <-> EtherCAT IO channel linking (full closed loop)

Complete the original goal: the tool now links the PLC %I*/%Q* variables to
real EtherCAT hardware channels, with the master enabled, and the build
passes unattended with no "needs sync master" popup.

Two missing pieces, found from Beckhoff's official EtherCATLinking.cs sample:
- Correct LinkVariables path format (roots prepended by the engine):
    PLC: TIPC^Shark^Shark Instance^PlcTask Inputs^GVL_Shark.bMotorRunSensor
    IO:  TIID^Device 1 (EtherCAT)^Term 1 (EK1100)^Term 2 (EL1008)^Channel 1^Input
  i.e. the mapped *instance* path, not the GVL declaration path used before.
- ITcPlcProject.CompileProject() must run first (cast TIPC^Shark) to generate
  the instance I/O image so the PLC-side path resolves.

Note: the instance/terminal tree nodes enumerate with ChildCount=0, but
LinkVariables resolves the paths by name regardless -- no Activate
Configuration / runtime target needed. Linking is idempotent (CompileProject
regenerates mappings, links re-apply cleanly every run).

Shipped:
- <Links> section in io-devices.xml (Link PlcVar=... IoChannel=...),
  parsed by IoManifestParser.ParseLinks into LinkSpec.
- VariableLinkEngine: CompileProject() then LinkVariables per declared link,
  reporting linked vs unresolved.
- Graceful fallback: if any link can't resolve, IoSyncEngine.DisableAllMasters
  disables the master so the build still stays green unattended.

Validated end-to-end twice against the live Shark project: 2 linked / 0
unresolved, master enabled, BUILD PASSED, no popup, no leaked devenv.
